raw_data.name: Night Swim Coffee Brevard
raw_data.typical_time_spent: People typically spend up to 2 hours here

reviews_data.review_text: Our drinks were very good, but it was more of the attitude of the person making the drinks. While we were waiting, he was huffing and puffing and glaring at us, and I felt as if I was somehow intruding when all I wanted was to pick up my drink. We never spoke to him or interacted in anyway, but I just felt the animosity coming off of him. Maybe he was having a bad day but when you’re making the drinks out in public, it’s probably best not to glare at the Customers. There are many choices in this area and I definitely will choose someplace else next time.
They have always served us promptly.
Parking is a tough one in NoDa! Regardless, the cozy environment of this Night Swim is a fresh escape from the busy roads. One of my favorite places to get coffee in Charlotte!

Found my new favourite coffee shop in NoDa/Optimist Park. Comfortable, clean, good service, great music (not too loud). Lots of windows, sunshine and nice view of the light rail. Food, coffee and tea were perfect. Try the Malabar herbal tea. Amazing. Keep up the good work.
Great coffee, the food is excellent, and the space is very well-designed and comfortable. I love coming to work from here.
Service was great at this Night swim and was very clean. Not many people on a Saturday afternoon even though it was nice out.

I was so excited when I found out Night Swim Coffee opened near me. I absolutely love their coffee and they always have amazing service! I had a cold brew with oat milk and their maple cardamom syrup. It was delicious. My boyfriend had their homemade coffee cake and really loved it. I only wish we could bring the dogs inside, but they have a decent outside area! Will definitely go back!
Coffee and food are delicious! However, the music is super loud and off putting, it's hard to do work or study. Maybe they do it on purpose so people don't linger?

In search of the best iced oat milk caramel latte in Charlotte. This one is the winner so far!!
Breakfast sandwich was delicious. Love how light and bright it is in there in the morning. Lots of plugs to charge computer.
Excellent coffee shop and great  atmosphere.
wonderful coffee shop!
Strange experience. We are pretty regular here but came on 4/9/24 at 9 am. No drip coffee. Said we would have a Latte as option. 14.00 later. Dunkin Coffee 3.39 for extra large. Go there instead.
I was feeling emotional and ended up at a vintage store. Then, came further down the street to find Night Swim. The atmosphere is as silky smooth as my cappuccino. Thoroughly enjoyable.
All around great spot
My go-to! I'm here at least once a week and the coffee/matcha/quiche NEVER disappoints. It's also a cozy spot to work from. Highly recommend!

Great little coffee shop, the employees are always so nice and everything there is delicious! My go to is a redeye with cream and sugar, it never disappoints. The matcha is also really good, the bagels are tasty. And they have seasonal drinks as well. I usually go a couple times a week, such a lovely place. This place is also exceptionally clean, probably as clean as a hospital lol. Can’t recommend enough :)

Beautiful cafe with great vibes. The coffee drinks are solid, and the food is great. I've been here many times. The sandwiches, quiche, baked goods, and overnight oats are all good. It's a great place to meet for coffee or to get some work done. The outdoor seating is a fun way to take in the neighborhood activity.

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Quiche of the Day, Overnight Oats, Blueberry Muffin

reviews_data.review_text:
the best coffee i’ve ever had🤌🏼
super cute inside🤎
Great aesthetic and atmosphere! Definitely a gem near NODA ✨️
Biscotti had a good portion; crispy crust and soft inner layer were great. Single origin coffee had very subtle flavor that one should take it as an espresso rather than americano.

Unfortunately the reason we went, ended up not working.  We had a NSC gift card to spend and the store didn't accept it. (must be used online).

The coffee is always delicious and very well done.
I guess we can chalk it up to inflation but the drinks, as good as they are, are hyperventilated.

I'll go back for a birthday or for a celebration.

Quiet shop with a nice atmosphere. Some gluten free breakfast options. The avocado blt on gf bread is super tasty. Overnight oats were good too. Coffee is solid but nothing special if you’re a coffee snob.

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Avocado Toast, Avocado blt, Overnight Oats

reviews_data.review_text: nice vibe, good coffee, great beans!
Vibes are 10/10. Bagels are literally so good. Coffee is incredible. Favorite spot in Charlotte!

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Everything Bagel Adders of Cream Cheese Avocado and Bacon Iced Caramel Latte on the Right

reviews_data.review_text: Excellent coffee shop with a good atmosphere for working or chatting. The coffee and espresso drinks are good. There’s a range of food items from bagel or focaccia  sandwiches to parfaits. While everything on the menu is tasty, the grits are the real standout item in my opinion. There are some tables outside in the shade, and there’s always a big bowl of water for dogs, which is nice for hot days.

I got the iced oatmilk matcha latte and my boyfriend got an iced brown sugar vanilla almond milk latte. Both were delicious! The staff was really nice and helpful. They also had plenty of vegan treats available which is awesome. Highly recommend
I am not a coffee drinker but their homemade yogurt parfait is to die for!!! It's so good. My husband enjoys their coffee though. I highly recommend Night Swim Coffee!

This coffee shop may look good but their coffee quality is not good. Their cappuccino was not hot enough, I had to ask them to heat it up for me again. The staff was not friendly at all. Other than coffee or tea, not much was offered.  Not worth coming back here especially with the poor way they make their coffee and the unfriendly staff.
Really good coffee and food selection
Thank you for the ginger iced tea rec!
Went there for a bagel with avocado spread and a brown sugar cold brew! The coffee is great but they gave me the wrong bagel and the avocado isn’t even ripe :(
Gorgeous decor on the inside, got a matcha latte and a caramel latte and both were good and well priced.
I bring my dog Trunks when I go. Amazing service! My go to is the Golden milk latte with zucchini bread. Yum.
Night Swim Coffee's latest location in The Joinery is a great addition to the neighborhood. Great space to work or meet up, serving delicious pour overs or the best iced caramel latte in the land.
